  "title": "Network Engineer (2-Year Renewable Contract)",
  "description": "<p></p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><p>Network and Firewall Support:</p><p>•\tAssist with the installation, configuration, and maintenance of network and firewall hardware and software.</p><p>•\tMonitor network and firewall performance, troubleshoot issues, and support resolution of outages.</p><p>•\tPerform routine maintenance, upgrades, and patching on network infrastructure.</p><p>•\tSupport LAN/WAN operations and ensure consistent connectivity across sites.</p><p>•\tMaintain accurate documentation of network configurations, changes, and standard procedures.</p><p>•\tCoordinate with internal departments and external vendors or stakeholders.</p><p>•\tTrack and maintain inventory of network and firewall-related assets under the Network Team.</p><p></p><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><p>•\tDiploma in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related discipline.</p><p>•\tMinimum 3 years of experience or internship in network engineering or IT support preferred.</p><p>•\t CCNA certification preferred</p><p>•\tStrong understanding of WAN, LAN, and network security</p><p>•\tExperience with Cisco networking technologies and/or Fortinet firewalls is an advantage</p><p>•\tBasic knowledge of networking concepts, protocols (e.g., TCP/IP, DNS, DHCP), and tools.</p><p>•\tFamiliarity with firewall technologies and basic network troubleshooting.</p><p>•\tStrong problem-solving skills and eagerness to learn.</p><p>•\tGood verbal and written communication skills.</p><p></p><p></p>",
